OL,3,CProminent loyalist in court over 'call
OL,4,Cto arms' social post
OL,6,FDetails emerged as the 53-year-old
OL,7,Fcommunity worker appeared at Belfast
OL,8,FMagistrates' Court charged with
OL,9,Fpublishing written material with
OL,10,Fintent to stir up hatred.
OL,12,FStitt, of Lord Warden's Court in
OL,13,FBangor, Co Down, was refused bail and
OL,14,Fremanded in custody until next month.
OL,16,FThe court heard a social media message
OL,17,Fon July 31 read: "Don't normally post
OL,18,Fanything on my page but with recent
OL,19,Fevents 'enough is enough' (and) 'get
OL,20,Fup and stand up'.
